  "title": "MineOS 98 | Windows 98 Theme",
  "description": "A simple GUI pack that gives most elements of the game a look taken from the classic OS Windows 98",
  "body": "<a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/members/eutatsu/projects\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/fp0jAho.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"96\" height=\"96\" /></a><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Eutatsu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://imgur.com/mkxvGi2.png\" width=\"192\" height=\"96\" /></a><img src=\"https://imgur.com/YkONue1.png\" width=\"160\" height=\"96\" /><img src=\"https://imgur.com/Xs64L0Q.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"96\" height=\"96\" /><a href=\"https://twitter.com/home\"><img src=\"https://imgur.com/gTeFCqY.png\" width=\"96\" height=\"96\" /></a><a href=\"https://ko-fi.com/eutatsu\"><img src=\"https://imgur.com/S2NA7zP.png\" width=\"96\" height=\"96\" /></a><br /><a href=\"https://www.planetminecraft.com/member/eutatsu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/oyKOpim.png\" width=\"96\" height=\"96\" /></a><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/mkxvGi2.png\" width=\"192\" height=\"96\" /><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/gYrOkol.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"160\" height=\"96\" /><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/mkxvGi2.png\" width=\"192\" height=\"96\" /><img src=\"https://imgur.com/Xs64L0Q.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"96\" height=\"96\" /><br><a href=\"https://discord.gg/xuHH6sNfnQ\"><img src=\"https://imgur.com/dcvjIu1.png\" width=\"96\" height=\"96\" /></a><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/mkxvGi2.png\" width=\"192\" height=\"96\" /><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/zHsTZvv.png\" width=\"160\" height=\"96\" /><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/mkxvGi2.png\" width=\"192\" height=\"96\" /><a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/texture-packs/mineos-98-high-contrast-theme\"><img src=\"https://imgur.com/0WcBG3m.png\" width=\"96\" height=\"96\" /></a><br /><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/Xs64L0Q.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"96\" height=\"96\" /><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"https://imgur.com/8kpDEhD.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"544\" height=\"96\" /><img src=\"https://imgur.com/Xs64L0Q.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"96\" height=\"96\" /><br /><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dQw4w9WgXcQ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://imgur.com/sAVrmLw.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"736\" height=\"96\" /></a>\n<p><span style=\"color: #008080;\">MineOS 98</span> is a GUI resource pack that changes all containers and some other elements of Minecraft and gives them a retro/nostalgic look based on that of Microsoft Windows 98.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The aesthetic of the pack is of&nbsp;<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">heavily cluttered</span> windows overlaping and tons of elements and icons, which <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">might get confusing if you're not at least a bit familiar with the Minecraft menus</span>, so if you're relatively new to the game, I'd recomned to first get used to the vanilla GUIs.</p>\n<p>This pack also freestlyes a bunch with the design of minecraft, some slots look out of place by one or two pixels, and most importantly, the placement of text is changed, to do this, I've had to change the language files, meaning that unless you want to see floating text all over the place, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>this pack works best when the language selected is UK English, US English or Spanish (More to be added in the future)</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>I might try to make a more simplified and easier on the eyes version in the future.</p>\n<p>I've also got plans to make variations with different Windows colour themes and perhaps even with different Operating Systems.</p>\n<p>Optifine features and a menu panorama are also ideas that are pending to introduce.</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">I will try my best</span> to port this to bedrock and to older versions.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Many of the icons used are <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">taken directly from Windows</span>&nbsp;98&nbsp;using the website <span style=\"color: #008080;\"><a style=\"color: #008080;\" href=\"https://win98icons.alexmeub.com/\"><span style=\"color: #008080;\">Windows</span> 98 Icon Viewer</a></span> and I take no credit in having created them.</p>",
